This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) because it investigates the capacity of mechanisms for compositional semantic parsing to describe relations between sentences and semantic representations. It is also likely to belong to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) because it deals with mechanisms for semantic parsing, which is a key task in natural language processing. The paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) because it discusses the capacity of neural systems for semantic parsing. Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the sub-categories of neural networks and learning (cs.NE) and systems and control (cs.SD) because it discusses the capacity of mechanisms to remember and process information.
